# DUAL LICENSING NOTICE

This project is dual-licensed to protect the core business logic while keeping the UI components open for educational and community use.

## 1. Restricted Core (Business Source License 1.1)

The backend logic, API routes, data ingestion, and AI automation components are licensed under the **Business Source License 1.1 (BSL 1.1)**.

- **Files affected:** `lib/`, `scripts/`, `app/api/`, `db/`
- **Permissions:** You may read, modify, and run this code for **non-commercial** purposes (e.g., learning, evaluation, portfolio demonstration).
- **Restrictions:** You **MAY NOT** use this code to build a competing SaaS product or for any commercial production use without permission.
- **Full Text:** See [LICENSE-BSL](./LICENSE-BSL)

## 2. Open Source UI (MIT License)

The frontend components, design system, and UI utilities are licensed under the **MIT License**.

- **Files affected:** `components/`, `app/globals.css`, public assets.
- **Permissions:** You are free to use, copy, modify, and distribute these components in your own projects, including commercial ones.
- **Full Text:** See [LICENSE-MIT](./LICENSE-MIT)

---

## Why this structure?

This is a portfolio project demonstrating complex SaaS architecture. The strict license on the backend prevents unauthorized commercial cloning of the core product value, while the permissive license on the frontend encourages sharing design patterns and UI components with the developer community.
